===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|亦|夕|t2=[[moon]]|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|abb1=y}}. {{och-l|夕}} may also serve as another phonetic component.

In the modern form, the phonetic {{l|zh|亦}} is distorted into {{Han compound|亠|亻|㇏}}, with the right-falling stroke {{l|zh|㇏}} merging into the semantic {{l|zh|夕}}.

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ja-n||night}} (STEDT); cognate with {{cog|lus|zân||night}}, {{cog|my|ည||night}}.

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} believes {{och-l|夜}} and {{och-l|夕}} are distinct as Tibeto-Burman keeps the etyma {{m|sit-pro|*ja-n||night}} and {{m|sit-pro|*rV-jak||day; day (24 hours); night}} strictly separate. However, {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}} suggest that {{l|zh|夜}} and {{l|zh|夕}} have clear etymological connections and thus reconstructs similar finals in both words.

